      • isLittleEndian

        public boolean isLittleEndian()
        If this port is a bus, it describes the endian-ness of how the bits in the bus vector are arranged. If the bus is little endian, LSB (least significant bit) is the rightmost bit (bus[7:0]). If the bus is not little endian (big endian), LSB is the left most bit (bus[0:7]).
        Returns:
        True if this bus is little endian, false otherwise. Not applicable for single bit ports.
